description:
Breakup over Texas



Aired on 12/29/2011, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 11 September 1991, Continental Express Flight 2574, an Embraer EMB 120 Brasilia, is nearing the end of its intra-state flight from Laredo, Texas to Houston. As the pilots are preparing to land, the aircraft tips into a dive and falls out of the sky as the left wing tears apart, all 14 people on board die.
